  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Forum on Industrial Development Issues</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As UNIDO&#x2019;s supreme policymaking organ held every two years, the General Conference determines, inter alia, the guiding principles and policies of the Organization, approves its budget and work programme and elects the members of its other policymaking organs. A forum on industrial development issues (FID) was introduced via GC.9/Res.1 into policymaking organ sessions with the intention of sharing a common understanding of development issues through the continued thematic examination of the fields relevant to UNIDO&#x2019;s technical cooperation activities that could impact the Organization&#x2019;s policy direction.

The immediate objective of the project is to strengthen partnerships and cooperation amongst Member States and partners of UNIDO on various aspects of ISID in the context by effectively organizing and ensuring the successful implementation of the GC&#x2019;s programme, with a particular focus on organizing the FID and securing high-level participation therein; organizing the ISID Forum and the Launch of the IDR 2019 within the framework of the GC; coordinating multiple topical side events; staging an on-site and virtual exhibition for UNIDO and its partners; conducting various communications and outreach activities to promote the GC; and carry out effective coordination between the various components of the GC to align with the main theme and messages of its eighteenth session.

Organized in Abu Dhabi, UAE, GC.18 will take place under the banner: &#x201C;Industry 2030 &#x2013; Innovate. Connect. Transform our Future.&#x201D;

By focusing on the innovation, connectivity and industrial transformation, GC.18 will serve as a forum to help prepare Member States, in particular developing and least developed countries (LDCs), for the potential benefits and challenges posed to their industries by the emerging phenomenon referred to as the Fourth Industrial Revolution or Industry 4.0.

Two standard events will be organized within the schedule of work of GC.18: the UNIDO Forum on Inclusive and Sustainable Industrial Development (ISID) and the Launch of the Industrial Development Report (IDR) 2019. These events will serve to showcase the unique role and success of UNIDO in convening multiple partners for development impact, as well as highlight UNIDO&#x2019;s position as the central node in the United Nations system for the collection and interpretation of data related to industrial development.

Interactive topical side events will round out the GC.18 programme, with the themes of &#x2018;innovation&#x2019;, &#x2018;connectivity&#x2019; and &#x2018;transformation&#x2019; refracted through today&#x2019;s development challenges and opportunities, including: industry 4.0; gender; green industry and circular economy; renewable energy; biotechnology; industrial parks, branding and sustainable cities; and migration, human security, youth employment and entrepreneurship training.

The project also supports the organization of the GC.18&#x2019;s exhibition, which will consist of a large on-site exhibition focusing on Member State and private sector representation; and a virtual exhibition to tie in remote participants to the proceedings of the GC. The exhibition will furthermore offers sponsorship opportunities for interested partners of UNIDO.

Proactive and continuous communication and coordination activities underlie the effective organization of the various elements of GC.18. This project will serve to also support the dissemination of key messages and the execution of a multi-channel media campaign, as well as coordination activities aligning various internal and external sets of partners and stakeholders, in order to achieve the maximum possible impact of the GC.18 proceedings and activities.</narrative>
  </description>
